{
  "texts": [
    "This sensitivity to instruction variability affects their ability to consistently generate accurate and contextually appropriate output.",
    "Additionally, as Speech LLMs are applied to increasingly complex tasks, their reasoning capabilities tend to degrade, particularly in understanding subtle, multi-step contexts.",
    "Moreover, Speech LLMs still have a long way to go in achieving true multitask generalizability, where a model can handle tasks it hasn't been explicitly trained on.",
    "At present, models often fail to perform certain tasks unless they have been specifically trained for them.",
    "Researchers are expected to focus on improving models' adaptability to diverse instruction formats, enhancing their reasoning capabilities, and enabling more seamless multitask learning across tasks the model has not been trained on.Another critical avenue for future work lies in extracting richer and finer acoustic information from speech."
  ]
}